CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 25, 1956, page 2, reads: "It's Like This - Mrs. Isadore Miles of Washington, D.C., explains her point of view to N. B. Patton, left, and T. B. Kennedy of Chattanooga, Tenn. The three were delegates to the American Teachers Federation. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two men and woman, from left: N. B. Patton, Isadore Miles, and T. B. Kennedy, wearing American Federation of Teachers name tags, standing in hallway of the Penn Sheraton Hotel
